>> servings: 2

Prepare the sauce in a big bowl: @garlic paste{2%tsp}, @salt{1%tsp}, @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, @vinegar{2%tbsp}, @chili oil{1%tsp}, and @sesame oil{1%tsp}. Whisk to combine and taste to adjust seasoning.

Use the side of a #Chinese cleaver{} to smack the @cucumbers{2}. Then cut them to bite-size pieces.

Combine the sauce with the cucumbers. Serve cold.
